INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (1773, 238, '2020-10-28 16:25:51', '2020-10-28 16:25:51', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":646,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"How to create a paper wallet?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":770,\"description\":\"<p>To create a paper wallet for Bitcoin, it is necessary to use an appropriate program that allows you to generate a public and private key. In this matter - just like other types of wallets - this one, too, must have unique two keys that somehow open up access to money.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A paper wallet can be generated via www.bitaddress.org.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>After launching the page where it is possible to generate a Bitcoin paper wallet, the system will ask the user to move the cursor over the dotted areas. This will generate the appropriate passwords and codes, so Private Key and Bitcoin Address, the first being a private key and the second a public one.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can also opt for wallet encryption, but this is an option that should be used by users experienced in this world. In the additional options of creating a crypted wallet you can also remove the graphic characters (Hide Art) and leave only the letter form. Under the &quot;Addresses to generate&quot; function there is a possibility to generate the expected number of key sets, while &quot;Addresses per page&quot; will allow you to determine the number of keys to be printed on one page.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The last step is to save and print your Bitcoin paper wallet. However, it should be remembered that if the investor wants to order a transfer from the paper wallet, he must first import the private key.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        770, 239, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (1774, 238, '2020-10-28 16:28:04', '2020-10-28 16:28:04', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":645,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Which crypto exchange is the best?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":771,\"description\":\"<p>You should always carefully check the costs of using a given platform (the amount of commission), the volume of transactions that it registers (the higher the higher the volume, the easier it will be for us to trade on it) and above all the security issues. In the latter we mean all the elements that can help us to protect our funds. It is worth checking whether, for example, the exchange offers multi-level authentication (2FA). An important issue for traders will also be the exchange&#39;s offers in terms of the multiplicity of trading pairs.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hacking still happens on the market. Therefore, it is also worth checking which entity is behind a given platform and what is its type (is it a company, if so, where it is registered). Additionally, it is worth to find out if the persons managing the stock exchange are open and searchable on social media, e.g. LinkedIn.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For beginner traders, i can recommend two exchanges, which are easy to use and at the same time safe. It&#39;s Binance and Coinbase. That&#39;s two best platforms for now in my opinion.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        771, 239, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
