        '{\"message\":{\"content\":660,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"What is vanity adress?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":785,\"description\":\"<p>Vanity address - it&#39;s a kind of crypto wallet address, which contains a personalized sequence of characters, readable to humans. An example of a traditional crypto wallet address is: 3P4glGUlpKJrgvj3n7GBgnLPqBdjVgf3jx. An example of a &quot;vanity&quot; address can be 3CCFOUNDBPzzD72PUXLzCkYAtGFYmK5Vynr33. For this address, it contains the word &quot;Ccfound&quot; which consists of five letters Base-58.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Creating a &quot;vanity&quot; address requires the user to generate and test millions of private keys until the right combination is created.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The difficulty of generating the desired address depends on its structure, i.e. letters and numbers contained in a sequence of characters. Each additional character in the &quot;vanity&quot; address increases the difficulty and time needed to generate it. Vanity&quot; addresses, which contain longer words, are usually created by specialized hardware, with multiple graphics processing units (GPUs).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Vanity&quot; addresses can be used to reinforce security measures, in the sense that a characteristic address makes it difficult for hackers to swap it and cheat those sending money.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Vanity addresses, however, can also create security gaps. They allow anyone to create a string of characters that resembles a different wallet address, making it possible to cheat money senders. Seeing a similar wallet address, they may not notice the difference and send money to the cheater instead of you.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        785, 239, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
