        '{\"message\":{\"content\":685,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"What is a HoneySwap and how to use it?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":807,\"description\":\"<p>&nbsp;Honeyswap it is a fork of Uniswap the popular decentralize exchange. The only difference is that Honeyswap is on the xDai sidechain instead of the Ethereum mainnet and therefore it only costs small fractions of a penny for each transaction fee. The problem you are facing is the same as what I had. You have to change the network in your Metamask on the top of the wallet when you see Ethereum Mainnet click and choose from the drop down box &ldquo;Custom RPC&rdquo;. Here you have all the details you need to put there : Network Name: <strong>xDai<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>New RPC URL:<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/rpc.xdaichain.com\\/\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"> <strong>https:\\/\\/rpc.xdaichain.com\\/<\\/strong><\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Chain ID: <strong>0x64<\\/strong> (100)<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Symbol: <strong>xDai<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Block Explorer URL:<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/blockscout.com\\/poa\\/xdai\\/\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"> <strong>https:\\/\\/blockscout.com\\/poa\\/xdai<\\/strong><\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>After you done that you are ready to use Honeyswap. Hopefully this is not too complicated for you. If you are facing more problems please let me know. I&#39;ll try to help you. Regards&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
