VALUES (2014, 233, '2020-12-10 11:52:32', '2020-12-10 11:52:32', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":715,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"What is the best staking pool for Cardano ADA ??\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":834,\"description\":\"<p>Hi Andi. I am a big fan of cardano and I&#39;ve done some research on staking pools. There is plenty of information which pool to choose. However I noticed these people don&#39;t look in more details about pools. Some of them say when you choose a lower fees pool you get more Ada rewards. No it doesn&#39;t mean you get more Ada it has changed since staking comes to mainet. Now we need to look for others factors which plays a big role here. First you have to look for a high amount of pledge volume at least 50k or above. Secondly cost per epoch is a fee taken from total rewards of the pool not individual. Pledge determinantes how many rewards you get. Higher pledge means higher rewards. If you delegate your ada to a small pool you might not get the rewards because the fee may take all profit. By delegating to a bigger pool you will get more rewards.&nbsp; Please check this website and see which pool you will like&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/adapools.org\\/\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\">https:\\/\\/adapools.org\\/<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
