INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2052, 246, '2020-12-16 13:27:07', '2020-12-16 13:27:07', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":716,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"What is a CME gap ?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":836,\"description\":\"<p>First of all it is necessary to explain what a CME is. Two brokers based in Chicago have launched Bitcoin futures some while ago - allowing the settlement of contracts in cash against USD. The first appeared on behalf of the Chicago Mercantile Exchange (CME) and the second from the Chicago Board Options Exchange (CBOE). These contracts are only traded during the trading hours of the exchange. Trading on these contracts raises more and more interest among investors. Many investors think that these contracts have a huge impact on traditional Bitcoin valuations. As we know, Bitcoin is traded 24 hours a day. CME gaps appear when Bitcoin price moves while the CME Bitcoin futures market is closed. Therefore, the gaps very often appear on weekends. The past shows that the CME gaps are 95% filled. Historically, every gap has finally been filled over time. Usually there are only a few open at a time, and when they are open it may or may not point to the next Bitcoin direction. Bitcoin CME gaps can be seen in the CME Futures Chart (! BTC) <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/uk.tradingview.com\\/chart\\/ZjRPt32d\\/\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\">https:\\/\\/uk.tradingview.com\\/chart\\/ZjRPt32d\\/<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        836, 228, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2053, 233, '2020-12-16 13:37:08', '2020-12-16 13:37:08', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":724,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"How to connect Ledger Nano X to Metamask??\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":837,\"description\":\"<p>I just figured out how to solve the issue in my case (ledger nano x, Windows 10, metamask on brave). What you need to do is plug your ledger nano x into the computer then click the metamask icon in your browser, then click the account selector circle at the upper right corner. Click connect hardware wallet. You will see it will load up a browser page, during this time you should unlock your nano with the pin.After open your ethereum app on the nano, go to settings, and the first thing you see at that point will be the toggle for allowing or disallowing contract data.You must ALLOW it. And then you can do whatever transaction you want to do. This time your ledger should show the transaction and you can accept it.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        837, 228, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
