INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2146, 235, '2021-01-21 14:31:05', '2021-01-21 14:31:05', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":613,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Why is it worth to differentiate investments?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":872,\"description\":\"<p>Diversification of capital is especially important for those who run their own businesses. Security of liquidity is something everyone strives for. The key here is the investment strategy. It is not worth putting all your capital in one service, industry or market. It is best to expand your operations into multiple branches that will differ in certain characteristics. In this way, when one segment will bring losses, another will become a security - and thus the financial damage will be minimized as much as possible.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When it comes to capital allocation, it is worth considering, among other things, precious metals (where, for example, a good supplement to gold is investment silver), real estate, as well as alternative investments, which have been very popular recently: works of art, whiskey or precious stones (e.g. diamonds).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At the beginning you should make a detailed analysis of your financial situation. This will help you choose the right investment tools and ways to invest your capital. The next step is to prepare an investment strategy, which will include hedging measures in order to minimize the loss of capital. Finally, you need to remember about the relation between risk and return on investment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It is worth mentioning here the theory of Harry Markowitz, who repeatedly stated that one should look for investments that, for a given rate of return, will involve the least risk or, for a given risk, will give the highest rate of return. These principles are particularly effective for businesspeople who want not only to reduce their investment risk, but also to get the highest possible returns from their investments.<br \\/>\\r\\n&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nAdditionally, it should be remembered that in any situation insurance will help us - and this is the function of investment gold. Practically every investor trading large sums of money deposits about 10% of their capital in gold in case of market turbulences.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        872, 189, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2147, 235, '2021-01-21 14:32:47', '2021-01-21 14:32:47', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":651,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Who is your investment guru?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":873,\"description\":\"<p>To me, a guru is anyone who meets the following conditions:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>1) first, it is important that the investor we want to emulate has a long track record in the stock market and has a good or very good records. &nbsp;In addition to investment track record, it is important that the guru matches our character. Some hints may be the decisions made by a large investor during crisis situations;<br \\/>\\r\\n2) when making investment decisions on the basis of the market guru, we need to prepare a reliable source of information, from which we will draw information about changes in the shareholding of companies of interest to us;<br \\/>\\r\\n3) the third point of the action plan concerns persistent copying of the chosen guru&#39;s moves. It is important to maintain the proportion of owned securities in the portfolio.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        873, 189, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2148, 236, '2021-01-21 14:34:27', '2021-01-21 14:34:27', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":609,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Bitcoin halving - what it is?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":874,\"description\":\"<p>On average, every four years we witness a phenomenon that shows the power of decentralization and autonomy of cryptocurrencies. It is halving, i.e. reducing BTC issuance by exactly half. The Bitcoin blockchain performs halving completely automatically, according to the specification of the network, every 210,000 blocks. The third halving took place on May 11, 2020 and reduced the reward for solving one block to 6.25 BTC from the previous 12.5 BTC. Halving BTC &nbsp;significantly reduces Bitcoin&#39;s inflation (which is currently around 1.8% per year).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It also affects the price of BTC, as the supply of BTC decreases in the market and miners (especially the smaller ones) are often on the verge of profitability. Those who can afford it start accumulating BTC and try to weather the temporary drop in profitability, hoping for big increases once the post-halving dust settles.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        874, 189, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2149, 233, '2021-01-21 14:38:03', '2021-01-21 14:38:03', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":724,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"How to connect Ledger Nano X to Metamask??\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":875,\"description\":\"<p>I will describe to you the entire process of connecting your hardware wallet in a few steps<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Step one is to launch the Metamask wallet. To do this, we find the fox icon in our browser&#39;s toolbar and click it. This will launch our wallet:<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>We enter our security password &nbsp;and then click the LOG IN button .<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>We are logged into the wallet. To add a hardware wallet we click on the avatar of our account located in the upper right log in.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A menu will appear from which we can choose Connect Hardware Wallet.&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>On the next screen we can choose what kind of hardware wallet we have and what we want to connect. In your case it will be Ledger.&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Before you choose it and click Connect, connect your hardware wallet to the computer. Activate it by entering your security PIN and enable the Ethereum application.&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>With the hardware wallet connected and the Ethereum application active, click Connect.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>And select Legacy (MEW\\/MYcrypto)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Then the list already displays my desired account. I select it and click the Unlock button.&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>On the screen we see the status of our hardware wallet. On the left side there is information about the tokens on the Ledger.&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n\"}}',
        875, 189, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2150, 228, '2021-01-21 14:40:01', '2021-01-21 14:40:01', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":726,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"How to fix pending transaction on Ethereum ??\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":876,\"description\":\"<p>It is very annoying when your transaction has a pending status for tens of minutes and you need to complete the transfer very quickly. Unfortunately, Ethereum does not provide a cancel button. You have to deal with it in a different way. A very simple way. Just overwrite the transaction, setting it at least 10% higher Gas than before. If the transaction has already fallen into the transaction field, it has been given certain nonce values and addresses you have entered. It is identified and unique based on these values. Because of this, we can resend the transaction with the same parameters, only changing the GWEI value. Namely, if your first transaction was sent with GWEI = 4, then now resend that transaction, to the same address and the same ETH amount, but change the GWEI to e.g. the preferred GWEI = 21. This should overwrite the transaction that falls into the transaction field and is caught by the miner quickly. If a transaction with a higher GWEI is caught, then the one with the lower GWEI will cease to exist because they have the same Nonce and the more profitable one has already been mined in the specified block.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        876, 189, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2151, 246, '2021-01-21 14:42:27', '2021-01-21 14:42:27', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":730,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"What are the crypto wallets? Do we actually need them?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":877,\"description\":\"<p>A cryptocurrency wallet is where we store our private keys. Cryptocurrencies don&#39;t leave their networks, so what determines ownership is access to a password that will allow us to transfer them. A private key is a long, random string of numbers and characters, practically impossible to remember. A cryptocurrency wallet is where we have it stored.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Example:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If I have 2 bitcoins and want to send them to Tom, I need to know his public address. It&#39;s like a letter that arrives in someone&#39;s mailbox - you need to know the address and provide it. The letter arrives in the mailbox, but in order for Tom to take it out, he must have a key to open it. If Andrew loses the key, he cannot get to the contents of the mailbox.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The difference between the letterbox key and the private key that allows us to access our cryptocurrencies is that the latter cannot be reset or recovered. There is no locksmith who is able to open our mailbox. If you lost access to your private key, you lost your cryptocurrencies. This is why wallets were created.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Cryptocurrency wallets are used to store private keys. &quot;Physically&quot; all bitcoins and other cryptocurrencies are located all the time in their networks - blockchains. Private keys are assigned to them, which make these funds have their exclusive owners.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It is worth mentioning that there are wallets designed exclusively for specific cryptocurrencies as well as those supporting multiple types of them. If you send a particular cryptocurrency to a wallet not intended for it, you will probably lose it.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        877, 189, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
