INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2160, 235, '2021-01-26 22:06:02', '2021-01-26 22:06:02', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":614,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Wallet for Litecoin - which one to choose?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":884,\"description\":\"<p>Ledger Nano S is the most popular hardware wallet available and supports Litecoin.<br \\/>\\r\\nIf you have a lot of Litecoin, this is the safest and most reliable way to store it. It not only allows you to control your private keys, but also to control them in an offline environment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It comes with a built-in OLED screen, a backup initial key, and a PIN code function. This way you can recover your funds in case something goes wrong with your hardware device.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Exodus is one of my favorite free wallets.<br \\/>\\r\\nIt is a multi-currency mobile wallet that supports 8 cryptocurrencies (including Litecoin).<br \\/>\\r\\nIt has a very interactive user interface and is backed by an active development team led by JP Richardson and Daniel Castagnoli.<br \\/>\\r\\nMost importantly, I like that Exodus&#39; ease of use is not compromised by a lack of security. It also provides its users with a one-click recovery system to restore a wallet using a 12-phrase recovery.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It even has a built-in ShapeShift converter for lovers of multiple cryptocurrencies. You can use this feature to exchange any of your currencies for another.<br \\/>\\r\\nExodus is available on Mac, Linux, and Windows.<br \\/>\\r\\nThey also have multiple exchange partners (not just ShapeShift), which means we can offer more exchangeable assets. Sourcing cryptocurrencies from different partners has made exchanging on Exodus faster and more reliable.<br \\/>\\r\\nThey also don&#39;t require a personal email address - an option for those who want an email backup link. You can use any email address - or none at all. The email is only used once to send the backup link. Privacy is very important to Exodus and they do not store any personal customer information - not even an email address.<br \\/>\\r\\nExodus users can also send funds and receive funds from smart contracts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        884, 239, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2161, 235, '2021-01-26 22:07:01', '2021-01-26 22:07:01', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":614,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Wallet for Litecoin - which one to choose?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":885,\"description\":\"<p>LoafWallet is the first iOS-only mobile wallet for Litecoin. It is not available for Android devices.<br \\/>\\r\\nIt was developed by Charlie Lee, the creator of LTC.<br \\/>\\r\\nThe Litecoin Association, a passionate group of volunteers who want to promote LTC, looks after the LoafWallet service.<br \\/>\\r\\nLoafWallet is an open-source HD wallet that allows you to restore funds using a 12-word backup key.<br \\/>\\r\\nIt also has a built-in feature that allows users to purchase LTC via Coinbase and store them in the Loaf wallet.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Electrum-LTC is a lightweight litecoin wallet that does not require downloading an entire block or waiting for syncing.<br \\/>\\r\\nIt is a dynamic wallet that provides its users with ease of use and security with a 12-bit security key. It is supported by SegWit and provides the additional feature of &quot;freezing&quot; an address (meaning you can no longer send funds from that address).<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        885, 189, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2162, 228, '2021-01-26 22:10:31', '2021-01-26 22:10:31', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":619,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Blockstack what is it ??\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":886,\"description\":\"<p>Blockstack is the company behind the blockchain Stack. Founded in 2013 and headquartered in New York City, Blockstack PBC has employees in Canada, Europe, and Asia. Blockstack&#39;s software is open source, with a global community of over 7,000 members.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Blockstack recently launched Testnet Stacks 2.0, an update that will allow developers and miners to participate in Blockstack&#39;s newest consensus mechanism, Proof of Transfer (PoX). I will discuss this topic in a moment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>What fascinates me most about BlockStack is their commitment to the bitcoin network, and the level of adoption that the network can already boast.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>BlockStack gets the consensus of the network, through a simple but very clever mechanism known as Proof-of-Transfer (PoX), and it is this mechanism that uses the bitcoin network and its security, to allow the Stack layer (blockchain from BlockStack) to enjoy a similar level of security. How it works?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The native asset on the BlockStack network is the coin STX, and a consensus protocol ties BTC to STX and STX to BTX on an economic incentive basis.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Miners who want to secure Blockstack use Bitcoin as a means to give them a chance to build and propagate a block on the Stacks network.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Who builds the next block in the Stacks network is decided in the form of a competition.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In order to participate in the contest to be selected as the leader to build the next block miners must send any amount of BTC to a designated address for what is known as the Rewards Set, or prize pool.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The more BTC they deposit, the higher their chances of being selected to produce the next block. But the size of the BTC deposit itself is not the only parameter here. The other parameter is VRF, or Verifiable Random Function. This is a cryptographic function (similar functions are used by Algorand and Cardano to secure their networks) which is a kind of lottery with cryptography behind its randomness, security and verifiability.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In a nutshell we can say that the size of the BTC deposit x VRF score = determines the chances of a miner to be chosen as a Block Leader who will build a block and join this block to the Stacks network. Why would such a miner &quot;lose&quot; valuable BTC and take part in such a lottery? Well, in order to win 500 STX coins = because that&#39;s how much a miner is rewarded for a block in this network. 500STX is additionally generated supply (minting) in the Stack network.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        886, 189, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2163, 239, '2021-01-26 22:13:46', '2021-01-26 22:13:46', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":720,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Which graphic card is the best for now?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":887,\"description\":\"<p>The best cards are those that are simply efficient and at the same time their power consumption is not big. So that mining is profitable. When buying a new graphics card &nbsp;we have to take into account not only the efficiency of the equipment but also its profitability. The costs that need to be taken into account are the cost of the card and electricity. Profit, of course, is how much we will earn after deducting all costs. Sometimes the most expensive graphics card can be less profitable than a cheaper one that has been on the market for some time...<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The cryptocurrency market is incredibly dynamic and that is why you need to constantly expand your knowledge about it. We need to analyze the rates that change from day to day. The prices of hardware are changing rapidly more than once. There are newer and newer graphic cards , with which currency mining is even easier. However, new, faster equipment and a larger number of people mining a given currency makes it more difficult to mine. That&#39;s why you need to constantly monitor the profitability of your investments.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        887, 235, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2164, 246, '2021-01-26 22:16:01', '2021-01-26 22:16:01', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":714,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"What will happen to my Ethereum if we shift to 2.0??\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":888,\"description\":\"<p>The release of Eth2.0 is initially completely indifferent to the current chain. It will continue to live its life. It will not have to go through any forks. Ether holders, or any other ERC-20 token, need do literally nothing. In the same way, all projects and Dapps running on the current Ethereum will continue to work. Everything remains the same. Ethereum continues to work the way it did.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The situation will change when we enter the second phase of the migration (most likely in couple years). At that time, the current Ethereum chain is to be incorporated into the ETH2.0 network as one of the shards. This will likely require an early hard fork and transition to a Proof of stake consensus mechanism. But for now, that&#39;s a long future thing.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        888, 235, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2165, 236, '2021-01-26 22:20:32', '2021-01-26 22:20:32', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":592,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Which cryptocurrency exchange is the best?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":889,\"description\":\"<p>For me, the best exchange is Poloniex, which is rated as one of the largest cryptocurrency exchanges in the world. It allows exchanges in as many as 80 different cryptocurrencies and 363 pairs. On this market, however, you cannot buy bitcoin and other currencies with traditional (fiat) money. However, this exchange is primarily intended for those looking to invest in other, less popular virtual currencies.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The way of making transactions on the Poloniex is important. For example, if a client wants to buy Dash for BTC (DASH\\/BTC) and doesn&#39;t have any other cryptocurrency in his wallet yet, he should buy bitcoin on other exchange and then send it to his private wallet address on Poloniex (it can be found in the Balances - Deposits &amp; Withdrawals tab). Then the client clicks Deposit next to the selected cryptocurrency. The client can transfer virtual coins from BitBay in the My Account -&gt; Withdrawal tab.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Due to its very large range of cryptocurrencies and simple and clear interface, Poloniex is good for exchanging more exotic cryptocurrencies paired with bitcoin. However, the inability to buy bitcoin on this exchange directly is a drawback for many people using this platform, so it is not always rated positively.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        889, 189, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2166, 239, '2021-01-26 22:24:29', '2021-01-26 22:24:29', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":720,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"Which graphic card is the best for now?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":890,\"description\":\"<p>Remember that when choosing a card for digging, you need to pay attention to the following criteria:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Power consumption - given in Watts - the amount of output current the card consumes during operation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Performance (hash rate) - given in Mh\\/s - the computing power that the card achieves under ideal conditions. Sometimes this value will be given in ranges, the ranges will depend on overclocking the card, flashing the bios and changes in power supply.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>As an additional factor of choice in all I would recommend creating by dividing the hash rate by the power consumption. Newer cards are usually more efficient than older models. This is the most important factor since electricity costs are a fixed cost for any miner and it is an extremely important element when evaluating the profitability of an investment. The more efficient the card the faster you will cover your investment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        890, 238, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2167, 235, '2021-01-26 22:25:25', '2021-01-26 22:25:25', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":720,\"content_parent_id\":\"887\",\"type_id\":2,\"articleTitle\":\"Which graphic card is the best for now?\",\"parentText\":\"<p>The best cards are those that are simply efficient and at the same time their power consumption is not big. So that mining is profitable. When buying a new graphics card &nbsp;we have to take into account not only the efficiency of the equipment but also its profitability. The costs that need to be taken into account are the cost of the card and electricity. Profit, of course, is how much we will earn after deducting all costs. Sometimes the most expensive graphics card can be less profitable than a cheaper one that has been on the market for some time...<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The cryptocurrency market is incredibly dynamic and that is why you need to constantly expand your knowledge about it. We need to analyze the rates that change from day to day. The prices of hardware are changing rapidly more than once. There are newer and newer graphic cards , with which currency mining is even easier. However, new, faster equipment and a larger number of people mining a given currency makes it more difficult to mine. That&#39;s why you need to constantly monitor the profitability of your investments.<\\/p>\\r\\n\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":891,\"description\":\"If you are going to use an AMD card then you need to download the AMD block chain driver to get the best performance. Without this driver you will experience huge performance drops on both old and new cards. Many AMD card users edit the BIOS to get better mining results with less power consumption. This is an advanced process that should only be attempted when you know what you are doing, but keep in mind that it cannot increase the mining capacity of the card to 50%.\"}}',
        891, 238, 5, 14, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2168, 246, '2021-01-26 22:28:20', '2021-01-26 22:28:20', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":687,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"How to multiply my bitcoin ?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":892,\"description\":\"<p>In recent weeks, the web has seen a spate of bots impersonating verified Twitter accounts. These bots claim to have received free money from celebrities such as the Winklevoss brothers or Elon Musk. The message includes information that if you too send your cryptocurrencies to the address provided, they will be doubled. Of course, such posts have nothing to do with the truth. This is one of the methods used by scammers to instill confidence in their victims. Some of the most popular scam wallets have even collected several thousand dollars each. The record holder received $400,000 in just a few days.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To find even more victims, scammers also usually use other platforms such as Twitch, Youtube or Facebook. Ripple tried to take action against Youtube for allowing scammers to distribute fake videos as paid advertisements. However, the initiative has not taken off and every now and then there are infromercials about more victims of a scam involving Elon Musk.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        892, 238, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
INSERT INTO `notices`
VALUES (2169, 246, '2021-01-26 22:31:29', '2021-01-26 22:31:29', 1,
        '{\"message\":{\"content\":687,\"type_id\":2,\"title\":\"How to multiply my bitcoin ?\",\"reason\":1,\"comment_id\":893,\"description\":\"<p>It is not possible to multiply cryptocurrencies in this way. To multiply your funds you had to start trading. If you start then always follow these golden tips:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Tips for making your investments more effective<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Investors of digital currency should keep track of legal changes, political and economic events, and technological developments around the world - as they have a big impact on the value of Bitcoin.<br \\/>\\r\\nThe most profitable investments are those that are well matched to our level of knowledge or experience. It is worth mentioning that people who are impulsive or risk averse should avoid CFDs and Binary Options trading.<br \\/>\\r\\nIt is best to spend some time understanding what bitcoin is and its specifics. More knowledge will always be useful to us.<br \\/>\\r\\nProper security of Bitcoin should be a priority for us. It is best to store our coins in a paper wallet or a physical wallet.<br \\/>\\r\\nIt is worth remembering that digital currencies attract a lot of amateurs tempted by the desire for quick profits. They trade emotionally which affects the overvaluation and undervaluation of Bitcoin.<br \\/>\\r\\nNever invest all the money you cannot afford to lose and diversify your money so that any loss is always the least painful.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}',
        893, 236, 5, 6, 0, 'en_US');
